{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idb8759ee1-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s1382d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1382d"},"text":"§ 1382d.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Rehabilitation services for blind and disabled individuals","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idb8759ee2-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s1382d/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Referral by Commissioner of eligible individuals to appropriate State agency","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"In the case of any blind or disabled individual who—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idb8759ee3-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s1382d/a/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" has not attained age 16; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idb8759ee4-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s1382d/a/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" with respect to whom benefits are paid under this subchapter,","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n\n"},{"tag":"continuation","attrib":{},"text":"the Commissioner of Social Security shall make provision for referral of such individual to the appropriate State agency administering the State program under subchapter V.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idb8759ee5-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s1382d/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Repealed. ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/97/35/tXXI/s2193/c/8/B"},"text":"Pub. L. 97–35, title XXI, § 2193(c)(8)(B)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1981-08-13"},"text":"Aug. 13, 1981","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/95/828"},"text":"95 Stat. 828","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idb8759ee6-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s1382d/c"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"c"},"text":"(c)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Repealed. ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/106/170/tI/s101/b/2/B"},"text":"Pub. L. 106–170, title I, § 101(b)(2)(B)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1999-12-17"},"text":"Dec. 17, 1999","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/113/1874"},"text":"113 Stat. 1874","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idb8759ee7-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s1382d/d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"d"},"text":"(d)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Reimbursement by Commissioner to State agency of costs of providing services to referred individuals","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Commissioner of Social Security is authorized to reimburse the State agency administering or supervising the administration of a State plan for vocational rehabilitation services approved under title I of the Rehabilitation Act of 1973 [","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t29/s720"},"text":"29 U.S.C. 720","children":[],"tail":" et seq.] for the costs incurred under such plan in the provision of rehabilitation services to individuals who are referred for such services pursuant to subsection (a), (1) in cases where the furnishing of such services results in the performance by such individuals of substantial gainful activity for a continuous period of nine months, (2) in cases where such individuals receive benefits as a result of "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s1383/a/6"},"text":"section 1383(a)(6) of this title","children":[],"tail":" (except that no reimbursement under this subsection shall be made for services furnished to any individual receiving such benefits for any period after the close of such individual’s ninth consecutive month of substantial gainful activity or the close of the month with which his or her entitlement to such benefits ceases, whichever first occurs), and (3) in cases where such individuals, without good cause, refuse to continue to accept vocational rehabilitation services or fail to cooperate in such a manner as to preclude their successful rehabilitation. The determination that the vocational rehabilitation services contributed to the successful return of an individual to substantial gainful activity, the determination that an individual, without good cause, refused to continue to accept vocational rehabilitation services or failed to cooperate in such a manner as to preclude successful rehabilitation, and the determination of the amount of costs to be reimbursed under this subsection shall be made by the Commissioner of Social Security in accordance with criteria determined by the Commissioner in the same manner as under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s422/d/1"},"text":"section 422(d)(1) of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idb8780ee8-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s1382d/e"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"e"},"text":"(e)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Reimbursement for vocational rehabilitation services furnished during certain months of nonpayment of insurance benefits","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"The Commissioner of Social Security may reimburse the State agency described in subsection (d) for the costs described therein incurred in the provision of rehabilitation services—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idb8780ee9-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s1382d/e/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":" for any month for which an individual received—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idb8780eea-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s1382d/e/1/A"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" benefits under section 1382 or 1382h(a) of this title;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idb8780eeb-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s1382d/e/1/B"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" assistance under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s1382h/b"},"text":"section 1382h(b) of this title","children":[],"tail":"; or"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idb8780eec-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s1382d/e/1/C"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"C"},"text":"(C)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" a federally administered State supplementary payment under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s1382e"},"text":"section 1382e of this title","children":[],"tail":" or "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/93/66/s212/b"},"text":"section 212(b) of Public Law 93–66","children":[],"tail":"; and"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idb8780eed-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s1382d/e/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":" for any month before the 13th consecutive month for which an individual, for a reason other than cessation of disability or blindness, was ineligible for—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idb8780eee-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s1382d/e/2/A"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" benefits under section 1382 or 1382h(a) of this title;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idb8780eef-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s1382d/e/2/B"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" assistance under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s1382h/b"},"text":"section 1382h(b) of this title","children":[],"tail":"; or"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"idb8780ef0-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s1382d/e/2/C"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"C"},"text":"(C)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" a federally administered State supplementary payment under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s1382e"},"text":"section 1382e of this title","children":[],"tail":" or "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/93/66/s212/b"},"text":"section 212(b) of Public Law 93–66","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idb8780ef1-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1935-08-14/ch531"},"text":"Aug. 14, 1935, ch. 531","children":[],"tail":", title XVI, § 1615, as added "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/92/603/tIII/s301"},"text":"Pub. L. 92–603, title III, § 301","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1972-10-30"},"text":"Oct. 30, 1972","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/86/1474"},"text":"86 Stat. 1474","children":[],"tail":"; amended "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/94/566/tV/s501/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 94–566, title V, § 501(a)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1976-10-20"},"text":"Oct. 20, 1976","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/90/2683"},"text":"90 Stat. 2683","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/96/272/tIII/s304"},"text":"Pub. L. 96–272, title III, § 304","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1980-06-17"},"text":"June 17, 1980","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/94/529"},"text":"94 Stat. 529","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/97/35/tXXI/s2193/a/4"},"text":"Pub. L. 97–35, title XXI, § 2193(a)(4)","children":[],"tail":", (c)(8), title XXIII, § 2344, "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1981-08-13"},"text":"Aug. 13, 1981","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/95/827"},"text":"95 Stat. 827","children":[],"tail":", 828, 867; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/98/369/dB/tVI/s2663/g/8"},"text":"Pub. L. 98–369, div. B, title VI, § 2663(g)(8)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1984-07-18"},"text":"July 18, 1984","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/98/1169"},"text":"98 Stat. 1169","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/98/460/s11/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 98–460, § 11(b)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1984-10-09"},"text":"Oct. 9, 1984","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/98/1806"},"text":"98 Stat. 1806","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/101/508/tV/s5037/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 101–508, title V, § 5037(a)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1990-11-05"},"text":"Nov. 5, 1990","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/104/1388-226"},"text":"104 Stat. 1388–226","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/296/tI/s107/a/4"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–296, title I, § 107(a)(4)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1994-08-15"},"text":"Aug. 15, 1994","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/108/1478"},"text":"108 Stat. 1478","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/105/33/tV/s5523"},"text":"Pub. L. 105–33, title V, § 5523","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1997-08-05"},"text":"Aug. 5, 1997","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/111/623"},"text":"111 Stat. 623","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/106/170/tI/s101/b/2/A"},"text":"Pub. L. 106–170, title I, § 101(b)(2)(A)","children":[],"tail":", (B), "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1999-12-17"},"text":"Dec. 17, 1999","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/113/1874"},"text":"113 Stat. 1874","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"idb8780ef2-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idb8780ef3-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"referencesInText","id":"idb8780ef4-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Rehabilitation Act of 1973, referred to in subsec. (d), is ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/93/112"},"text":"Pub. L. 93–112","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1973-09-26"},"text":"Sept. 26, 1973","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/87/355"},"text":"87 Stat. 355","children":[],"tail":". Title I of the Rehabilitation Act of 1973 is classified generally to subchapter I (§ 720 et seq.) of chapter 16 of Title 29, Labor. For complete classification of this Act to the Code, see Short Title note set out under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t29/s701"},"text":"section 701 of Title 29","children":[],"tail":" and Tables."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/93/66/s212/b"},"text":"Section 212(b) of Public Law 93–66","children":[],"tail":", referred to in subsec. (e)(1)(C), (2)(C), is "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/93/66/s212/b"},"text":"section 212(b) of Pub. L. 93–66","children":[],"tail":", title II, "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1973-07-09"},"text":"July 9, 1973","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/87/155"},"text":"87 Stat. 155","children":[],"tail":", which is set out as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s1382"},"text":"section 1382 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"idb8780ef5-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1999—Subsec. (a). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/106/170/s101/b/2/A"},"text":"Pub. L. 106–170, § 101(b)(2)(A)","children":[],"tail":", amended subsec. (a) generally. Prior to amendment, subsec. (a) read as follows: “In the case of any blind or disabled individual who—"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"“(1) has not attained age 65, and","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"“(2) is receiving benefits (or with respect to whom benefits are paid) under this subchapter,","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"the Commissioner of Social Security shall make provision for referral of such individual to the appropriate State agency administering the State plan for vocational rehabilitation services approved under title I of the Rehabilitation Act of 1973, or, in the case of any such individual who has not attained age 16, to the State agency administering the State program under subchapter V of this chapter, and (except for individuals who have not attained age 16 and except in such other cases as the Commissioner may determine) for a review not less often than quarterly of such individual’s blindness or disability and his need for and utilization of the services made available to him under such plan.”","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (c). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/106/170/s101/b/2/B"},"text":"Pub. L. 106–170, § 101(b)(2)(B)","children":[],"tail":", struck out subsec. (c) which read as follows: “Every individual age 16 or over with respect to whom the Commissioner of Social Security is required to make provision for referral under subsection (a) of this section shall accept such services as are made available to him under the State plan for vocational and rehabilitation services approved under title I of the Rehabilitation Act of 1973; and no such individual shall be an eligible individual or eligible spouse for purposes of this subchapter if he refuses without good cause to accept services for which he is referred under subsection (a) of this section.”"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1997—Subsec. (d). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/105/33/s5523/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 105–33, § 5523(2)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “the Commissioner” for “him” after “determined by” in last sentence."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/105/33/s5523/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 105–33, § 5523(1)","children":[],"tail":", which directed insertion of comma after “subsection (a)(1)” in first sentence, was executed by making the insertion after “subsection (a)” to reflect the probable intent of Congress."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1994—Subsec. (a). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/296"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–296","children":[],"tail":" in closing provisions substituted “Commissioner of Social Security” for “Secretary” and “the Commissioner may” for “he may”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (c). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/296"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–296","children":[],"tail":" substituted “Commissioner of Social Security” for “Secretary”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (d). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/296"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–296","children":[],"tail":" substituted “The Commissioner of Social Security is” for “The Secretary is”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (e). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/296"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–296","children":[],"tail":" substituted “Commissioner of Social Security” for “Secretary” in introductory provisions."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1990—Subsec. (e). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/101/508"},"text":"Pub. L. 101–508","children":[],"tail":" added subsec. (e)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1984—Subsecs. (a), (c). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/98/369/s2663/g/8"},"text":"Pub. L. 98–369, § 2663(g)(8)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “title I of the Rehabilitation Act of 1973” for “the Vocational Rehabilitation Act”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (d). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/98/460/s11/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 98–460, § 11(b)","children":[],"tail":", designated existing provisions of first sentence as cl. (1), added cls. (2) and (3), and inserted requirement that the determination that the vocational rehabilitation services contributed to the successful return of an individual to substantial gainful activity and the determination that an individual, without good cause, refused to continue to accept vocational rehabilitation services or failed to cooperate in such a manner as to preclude successful rehabilitation be made by the Commissioner of Social Security in accordance with criteria determined by him in the same manner as under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s422/d/1"},"text":"section 422(d)(1) of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/98/369/s2663/g/8"},"text":"Pub. L. 98–369, § 2663(g)(8)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “title I of the Rehabilitation Act of 1973” for “the Vocational Rehabilitation Act”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1981—Subsec. (a). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/97/35/s2193/c/8/A"},"text":"Pub. L. 97–35, § 2193(c)(8)(A)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “State agency administering the State program under subchapter V of this chapter (except for individuals who have not attained age 16 and except in such other cases” for “appropriate State agency administering the State plan under subsection (b) of this section, and (except in such cases”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (b). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/97/35/s2193/c/8/B"},"text":"Pub. L. 97–35, § 2193(c)(8)(B)","children":[],"tail":", struck out subsec. (b) which provided criteria for approval of State plans."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (d). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/97/35/s2344"},"text":"Pub. L. 97–35, § 2344","children":[],"tail":", substituted “is authorized to reimburse” for “is authorized to pay to”, “for the costs incurred” for “the costs incurred”, and “individuals who are referred for such services pursuant to subsection (a) if such services result in their performance of substantial gainful activity which lasts for a continuous period of nine months” for “individuals referred for such services pursuant to subsection (a)” and inserted provision that determination of the amount to be reimbursed be made by the Commissioner of Social Security in accordance with criteria determined by him in the same manner as under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s422/d/1"},"text":"section 422(d)(1) of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (e). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/97/35/s2193/c/8/B"},"text":"Pub. L. 97–35, § 2193(c)(8)(B)","children":[],"tail":", struck out subsec. (e) which provided for payment by the Secretary to a State agency charged with administering a State plan under subsec. (b), of the costs incurred each fiscal year from "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1976-09-30"},"text":"Sept. 30, 1976","children":[],"tail":", to "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1982-10-01"},"text":"Oct. 1, 1982","children":[],"tail":", in carrying out such State plan."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (e)(1). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/97/35/s2193/a/4/A"},"text":"Pub. L. 97–35, § 2193(a)(4)(A)","children":[],"tail":", inserted “and subject to section 2194(b)(3) of the Maternal and Child Health Services Block Grant Act”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"